      • KEY_REPLACER_TIME_TO_WAIT_BEFORE_SENDING_LAST_COMMAND

        public static final int KEY_REPLACER_TIME_TO_WAIT_BEFORE_SENDING_LAST_COMMAND
        In sticky mode, this delay will dictate how much the system waits before sending the last command. This delay is required to simulate key press because Gdx will only consider a key as being pressed once it is released. The unit is microsecond.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • KEY_REPLACER_TIME_TO_WAIT_BETWEEN_TWO_COMMANDS

        public static final int KEY_REPLACER_TIME_TO_WAIT_BETWEEN_TWO_COMMANDS
        In sticky mode, when there are no new command, this delay will dictate how much the system waits between two commands. The unis is microsecond.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
